<section class="py-14 md:py-20 bg-surface">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 font-display">Open source, community governed</h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        OwnPulse is open source and run as a cooperative. The code is public. The architecture
        decisions are public. Members elect the board. There are no investors deciding what
        features get built or what happens with your data.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        If you want to run it yourself, you can — the self-hosting guide has everything you need.
        But you don't have to. The hosted platform is the default experience, built and maintained
        by the community.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/ownpulse/ownpulse"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md border-2 border-neutral-300 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 hover:border-neutral-500 hover:text-neutral-900 transition-colors"
      >
        GitHub repository
      </a>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/ownpulse/ownpulse/blob/main/docs/guides/self-hosting.md"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md border-2 border-neutral-300 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 hover:border-neutral-500 hover:text-neutral-900 transition-colors"
      >
        Self-hosting guide
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
